WEBVTT

00:09.349 --> 00:10.329
(CAR HORN TOOTS)

00:10.429 --> 00:12.769
(DOM SINGS) ♪ Bah-bah-bah-bah

00:12.869 --> 00:15.369
♪ Bah-bah-bah-bah

00:15.469 --> 00:16.609
♪ Bah-bah-b... ♪

00:16.709 --> 00:18.809
Jesus Christ! Who are you?

00:18.909 --> 00:21.609
Hey, man.
I didn't mean to scare you.

00:21.709 --> 00:24.289
-I'm Levi, Garry's son.
-What are you doing here?

00:24.389 --> 00:26.929
-He didn't call you?
-About what?

00:27.029 --> 00:29.369
This is awkward. Um...

00:29.469 --> 00:31.409
I need the apartment back.

00:31.509 --> 00:34.809
-When?
-Well, now-ish.

00:34.909 --> 00:36.488
What about Turtle?

00:36.588 --> 00:38.008
Turtle?

00:38.108 --> 00:40.728
You've got to watch him
on the architraves.

00:40.828 --> 00:42.768
He likes to chew through
lead paint,

00:42.868 --> 00:45.408
which is an expensive habit.

00:45.508 --> 00:47.128
(TURTLE CHIRPS)

00:47.228 --> 00:49.908
-Shut the window!
-(CHIRPS)

00:57.708 --> 01:00.608
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

01:00.708 --> 01:03.708
(BALLAD PLAYS SOFTLY)

01:09.228 --> 01:10.527
Hi.

01:10.627 --> 01:12.007
-Angela, hi.
-Hi.

01:12.107 --> 01:13.487
-So pleased you came.
-Hello.

01:13.587 --> 01:16.047
(STAMMERS)
You were my daughter's

01:16.147 --> 01:17.607
favourite teacher at Jubilee.

01:17.707 --> 01:20.807
-Oh, wow.
-Yeah.

01:20.907 --> 01:23.487
Did your daughter set us up?

01:23.587 --> 01:25.287
No, no,
I just found you on the app

01:25.387 --> 01:27.367
and then we kind of
worked it out.

01:27.467 --> 01:33.007
Oh. Well, this is
my first, um, dating app date.

01:33.107 --> 01:35.047
First date since I split

01:35.147 --> 01:38.087
with my partner of 25 years,
actually.

01:38.187 --> 01:40.927
-My daughter was not involved.
-Hm.

01:41.027 --> 01:43.967
All right, well,
what do you wanna know?

01:44.067 --> 01:45.166
Uh...

01:45.266 --> 01:47.366
You know, divorced five years,

01:47.466 --> 01:48.966
townhouse in Burwood,

01:49.066 --> 01:51.206
border collie - Louie,

01:51.306 --> 01:54.646
um, two kids at uni
studying literature.

01:54.746 --> 01:58.646
Oh, that's refreshingly
non-vocational.

01:58.746 --> 02:01.166
I'm pleased
I didn't raise bankers.

02:01.266 --> 02:03.966
-Are you a banker?
-Lawyer.

02:04.066 --> 02:07.286
I work for
the Refugee Action Centre.

02:07.386 --> 02:09.246
(BOTH LAUGH)

02:09.346 --> 02:11.046
(LAUGHS) What?

02:11.146 --> 02:15.606
That sounds like a fake job
that you tell women on dates.

02:15.706 --> 02:19.445
-Would you like a drink?
-Yeah. That would be lovely.

02:19.545 --> 02:21.725
-What would you like?
-I don't know. Think I might...

02:21.825 --> 02:24.605
Should we get a...get a bottle
or two glasses?

02:24.705 --> 02:27.205
-Yeah, I like red. You like red?
-Yeah, I like... I like red.

02:27.305 --> 02:28.525
-I like shiraz.
-I like shiraz.

02:28.625 --> 02:29.765
Oh, snap!

02:29.865 --> 02:32.325
-SANTI: Thanks, guys.
-ZAC: Good.

02:32.425 --> 02:33.805
SANTI: It means the world to me.

02:33.905 --> 02:35.445
-(BABY CRIES)
-TALIA: You could stay.

02:35.545 --> 02:38.245
I know, but, you know, you've
got to do what you've got to do.

02:38.345 --> 02:42.205
Adulthood is the absolute worst.
I mean, why rush it, Santi?

02:42.305 --> 02:43.845
It's time to get out there, man.

02:43.945 --> 02:45.725
-Brave new world.
-(BABY GRIZZLES)

02:45.825 --> 02:47.645
So, what are you gonna do?

02:47.745 --> 02:51.985
Uh, Vince's cousin, actually,
he's a tradie. He got me a job.

02:53.985 --> 02:55.964
Formal.

02:56.064 --> 02:57.964
Muck-up day.

02:58.064 --> 02:59.644
Schoolies.

02:59.744 --> 03:02.764
It just feels like
everything's changing so fast.

03:02.864 --> 03:05.544
Things can't stay the same
forever, I guess.

03:07.584 --> 03:09.284
MADISON: Oh, you are
still talking to me.

03:09.384 --> 03:11.244
ZAC: It's been a pleasure.

03:11.344 --> 03:13.284
-(BABY GRIZZLES)
-SANTI: Bring it in, guys.

03:13.384 --> 03:15.084
BOY: Hope that stupid baby's
going too.

03:15.184 --> 03:17.324
Bro, fuck off.
J's not going anywhere.

03:17.424 --> 03:19.004
She is, actually.

03:19.104 --> 03:20.884
What?

03:20.984 --> 03:23.124
It is her last day.

03:23.224 --> 03:25.804
Whoa! End of an era!

03:25.904 --> 03:29.123
What? Wait. No.

03:29.223 --> 03:32.183
Yeah, it only really worked
with both of us here, so...

03:33.263 --> 03:35.263
(SIGHS) I'm talking to your dad.

03:37.423 --> 03:39.423
Come here, bro.

03:40.223 --> 03:45.063
-Hey, may I borrow you?
-Yes, of course. (GIGGLES)

03:49.903 --> 03:52.743
-You ready?
-Yep. (CLEARS THROAT)

04:00.303 --> 04:02.803
-Reems?
-Um...

04:02.903 --> 04:04.882
It says,

04:04.982 --> 04:06.402
"Thank you
for your application

04:06.502 --> 04:08.842
"to the four-week Canberra
summer internship program.

04:08.942 --> 04:11.682
"The quality of candidates
was extraordinarily high

04:11.782 --> 04:14.902
"and we...regret that
your application was not..."

04:18.142 --> 04:20.662
-OK.
-I'm so sorry, Ol.

04:22.182 --> 04:26.142
You know, the right thing will
happen. This just wasn't it.

04:28.222 --> 04:30.222
Yep.

04:30.662 --> 04:32.762
-It's OK.
-It's OK.

04:32.862 --> 04:37.062
Indiana, do I have
your assessment? Great.

04:39.701 --> 04:41.321
Oh.

04:41.421 --> 04:44.741
I'm never gonna get to
where I wanna go.

04:46.461 --> 04:49.461
Oh, of course you are.

04:50.661 --> 04:52.001
How do you know?

04:52.101 --> 04:55.521
'Cause you're my daughter.

04:55.621 --> 04:59.081
Unless you're planning on
dropping out of school,

04:59.181 --> 05:02.641
but I think one parent without
a high school qualification

05:02.741 --> 05:04.801
is enough for my granddaughter,
thank you very much.

05:04.901 --> 05:07.161
Don't tell Santi I said that.

05:07.261 --> 05:10.281
Oh, my God. Coming from you?

05:10.381 --> 05:12.881
You know, let's talk about

05:12.981 --> 05:14.720
the time that you got drunk
at J's christening

05:14.820 --> 05:17.040
and I had to hold your hair back
while you vomited.

05:17.140 --> 05:19.520
Or, I don't know, when you spent
thousands of dollars

05:19.620 --> 05:23.800
on someone's pet bird instead of
your granddaughter's future.

05:23.900 --> 05:26.920
Or how we had to deal with your
bullshit crush on Santi's dad,

05:27.020 --> 05:28.680
basically breaking up
his family.

05:28.780 --> 05:31.140
You are the worst mother alive.

05:36.020 --> 05:39.560
Look, I'm sure
she didn't mean it.

05:39.660 --> 05:41.880
Like, things have been tough
for Ol.

05:41.980 --> 05:45.120
Yeah, well, you couldn't
fault her for her accuracy.

05:45.220 --> 05:47.220
-(BOTH GROAN)
-(PHONE CHIMES)

05:48.340 --> 05:50.199
Who's this?

05:50.299 --> 05:52.299
No-one.

05:53.019 --> 05:53.959
Hm?

05:54.059 --> 05:56.139
I went on a date.

05:58.139 --> 05:59.839
What? With who?

05:59.939 --> 06:04.239
Um, a lovely school dad.
Divorced.

06:04.339 --> 06:07.779
He wrote a book on refugee law.

06:10.099 --> 06:11.239
What?

06:11.339 --> 06:14.379
You were the one who told me
to get on Bumble.

06:16.059 --> 06:18.439
Well, that was before
Granddad died

06:18.539 --> 06:22.399
and you guys kind of started
hanging out again.

06:22.499 --> 06:24.998
How do you think Dad's gonna
feel about this?

06:25.098 --> 06:28.438
Well, your dad and I
are separated.

06:28.538 --> 06:29.798
-You know that.
-Really?

06:29.898 --> 06:34.438
And why did you choose
this specific moment in time

06:34.538 --> 06:36.078
to go on a date, Mum?

06:36.178 --> 06:40.718
Because I am a free adult human.
I'm allowed.

06:40.818 --> 06:44.318
I'm really disappointed in you,
Mum.

06:44.418 --> 06:47.918
I was following your advice!

06:48.018 --> 06:50.398
Why would you do that? (SCOFFS)

06:50.498 --> 06:53.218
I don't know
what I'm talking about.

06:55.298 --> 06:59.437
Oh, my God! These fucking kids!

06:59.537 --> 07:01.637
YOUNG LIPZ:
♪ Baby, I was made for this

07:01.737 --> 07:04.157
♪ I'm not in love
but I got love for the streets

07:04.257 --> 07:07.197
♪ They said it wouldn't
make a man out of me... ♪

