07:31.137 --> 07:33.216
Ita.

07:34.576 --> 07:37.276
(CHUCKLES) You can't
do this every morning.

07:37.376 --> 07:39.416
I know.

07:40.496 --> 07:42.496
OK.

07:43.696 --> 07:45.196
-Mwah! I love you.
-I love you too.

07:45.296 --> 07:47.396
SANTI: OK, OK.

07:47.496 --> 07:50.556
Ita, are you sure about this?
Three days a week is a lot.

07:50.656 --> 07:54.236
It is not enough for
my sorpresa.

07:54.336 --> 07:56.116
(KISSES)

07:56.216 --> 07:58.556
-Ey. (SCOFFS)
-What?

07:58.656 --> 08:02.836
The people at the shop
will think she's a boy again.

08:02.936 --> 08:05.276
We need to get her ears pierced.

08:05.376 --> 08:08.895
Pierced? No. No. Definitely not.

08:14.815 --> 08:18.835
Ita, what do you think about
Santi leaving school?

08:18.935 --> 08:22.355
Men like to earn a living
for their family.

08:22.455 --> 08:24.595
It's what they do.

08:24.695 --> 08:29.315
So, am I supposed to be
some sort of kept wife?

08:29.415 --> 08:32.395
I don't understand why men
get to have kids,

08:32.495 --> 08:34.715
but their life barely changes.

08:34.815 --> 08:37.155
His life change a lot.

08:37.255 --> 08:39.155
He left school.

08:39.255 --> 08:42.315
He doing it for you
and Sorpresa.

08:42.415 --> 08:45.034
But I never asked him to be
some big breadwinner

08:45.134 --> 08:46.914
and leave me holding the baby.

08:47.014 --> 08:50.394
I'm holding the baby.

08:50.494 --> 08:52.534
ANGIE: Hey!

08:54.654 --> 08:57.394
-Hey! How are you?
-Good.

08:57.494 --> 09:00.074
-I made these posters.
-(LAUGHS)

09:00.174 --> 09:02.474
-Oh, sorry. Sorry.
-Nice. (LAUGHS)

09:02.574 --> 09:05.814
Um, no, I'm sure we'll find him.

09:06.814 --> 09:08.514
I went on a date.

09:08.614 --> 09:09.994
Oh.

09:10.094 --> 09:12.194
Yeah, I just wanted to be
upfront with you.

09:12.294 --> 09:14.194
He's a refugee lawyer.

09:14.294 --> 09:16.874
-Oh, that's...that's great.
-Yeah. (CHUCKLES)

09:16.974 --> 09:21.133
Good for you. I hope he's great.

09:23.373 --> 09:27.513
-Wonderful news.
-(GASPS) Oh, is that Turtle?

09:27.613 --> 09:30.653
Oh, nah. It's just a leaf.

09:31.973 --> 09:34.153
Turtle?

09:34.253 --> 09:36.253
Turtie-turt-turts!

09:37.373 --> 09:39.373
Come home.

09:42.373 --> 09:44.193
New kid, I've got a job for you.

09:44.293 --> 09:46.293
SANTI: All right, coming.

09:46.853 --> 09:48.753
-What is it?
-Battery's flat.

09:48.853 --> 09:51.273
-Can you jump-start it?
-Uh, yeah.

09:51.373 --> 09:54.672
What I need you to do is run it
like this until it clicks over.

09:54.772 --> 09:56.832
-Fast, but.
-OK.

09:56.932 --> 09:59.192
On the road as fast as you can.

09:59.292 --> 10:01.632
Uno, dos, tres. Go for it.

10:01.732 --> 10:03.732
(BLADE RATTLES)

10:04.972 --> 10:06.912
-Did you feel it?
-Uh, sort of.

10:07.012 --> 10:08.792
You just need to hit it
with some momentum.

10:08.892 --> 10:11.152
OK. Was that not enough?

10:11.252 --> 10:12.952
Yeah, yeah. Once it clicks,
you're on your way.

10:13.052 --> 10:15.052
SANTI: All right.

10:15.692 --> 10:16.912
-(SANTI GRUNTS)
-MAN: That was close.

10:17.012 --> 10:18.472
I could feel that.
Did you feel it?

10:18.572 --> 10:20.152
-SANTI: That was close?
-Yeah, but you need to...

10:20.252 --> 10:21.352
Yeah, I thought
I felt something.

10:21.452 --> 10:22.792
-Use the pows. Yeah.
-Yeah.

10:22.892 --> 10:24.432
-(BLADE RATTLES)
-Ándale!

10:24.532 --> 10:26.592
(LAUGHS) Yeah!
Faster, pretty boy!

10:26.692 --> 10:30.011
(TRADESMEN LAUGH)

10:32.331 --> 10:34.031
-Yeah, good one.
-(LAUGHS) Come on.

10:34.131 --> 10:35.231
(LAUGHTER CONTINUES)

10:35.331 --> 10:37.511
-Hope you enjoyed that.
-You all right?

10:37.611 --> 10:40.531
-MAN: Viral, Santi.
-SANTI: Yeah, fuck off.

10:41.771 --> 10:43.811
You should have seen
what I made him do.

10:59.291 --> 11:01.291
ROSA'S MOTHER: Ah.

11:26.610 --> 11:28.610
(CRIES)

11:31.130 --> 11:33.130
(BREATHES RAPIDLY)

11:35.010 --> 11:37.009
-(DREAMY, MELANCHOLY MUSIC)
-(FAINT SINGING)

11:48.409 --> 11:52.069
-(WOMAN SINGS IN DISTANCE)
-(BIRDSONG)

11:52.169 --> 11:54.209
(MARIA SINGS IN SPANISH)

12:16.768 --> 12:19.768
(MARIA CONTINUES SINGING
IN SPANISH)

12:37.208 --> 12:39.548
(SIGHS)

12:39.648 --> 12:42.668
(SIREN WAILS IN DISTANCE)

12:42.768 --> 12:45.108
I feel now's the time
to tell you

12:45.208 --> 12:46.827
that I've actually been doing

12:46.927 --> 12:51.507
a lot of self-realisation
lately.

12:51.607 --> 12:54.867
Oh, right. About Birdie?
The Birdie thing?

12:54.967 --> 12:56.827
And us, though.

12:56.927 --> 13:00.847
But...probably Baby J.

13:02.807 --> 13:06.627
I don't remember our kids
being this much work

13:06.727 --> 13:08.027
when they were babies.

13:08.127 --> 13:09.627
(SCOFFS)

13:09.727 --> 13:12.427
-Seriously?
-I know.

13:12.527 --> 13:15.927
But it made me realise
that I...

13:18.007 --> 13:21.506
..wasn't much help early on.

13:21.606 --> 13:23.786
Early on?

13:23.886 --> 13:27.906
Well, till they were teenagers.

13:28.006 --> 13:30.466
No, you weren't.

13:30.566 --> 13:32.566
Yeah, I just said that.

13:33.686 --> 13:35.686
My point is...

13:37.086 --> 13:39.086
..I want you
to find happiness...

13:40.206 --> 13:42.966
..with this lawyer bloke
or whomever.

13:45.526 --> 13:47.966
I want you to be happy.

13:50.006 --> 13:53.586
(TURTLE CHIRPS)

13:53.686 --> 13:57.265
Oh, my God. Dom, look, look,
look, look, look.

13:57.365 --> 14:00.385
Where?
In the branch! Turtie!

14:00.485 --> 14:02.825
-(TURTLE CHIRPS)
-ANGIE: Turtle!

14:02.925 --> 14:04.905
-It's...
-DOM: Oh, it definitely is.

14:05.005 --> 14:08.145
-Turtle! Turt...
-(CALLS)

14:08.245 --> 14:10.545
-Do the thing. (WHISTLES)
-(SQUAWKS)

14:10.645 --> 14:12.645
Turtle!

14:15.645 --> 14:17.625
(TURTLE CHIRPS)

14:17.725 --> 14:19.725
We can't, can we?

14:20.565 --> 14:22.565
Oh!

14:27.045 --> 14:30.185
You think
that really was Turtle?

14:30.285 --> 14:32.624
I choose to think so.

14:32.724 --> 14:34.264
Oh.

14:34.364 --> 14:37.724
Well, I guess we won't
be needing this, then.

14:42.924 --> 14:44.924
What?

14:45.564 --> 14:47.604
What if you stay?

14:48.764 --> 14:50.764
What?

14:51.324 --> 14:53.984
I honestly don't know
if it will work, but...

14:54.084 --> 14:56.664
..you're my best friend.

14:56.764 --> 14:58.904
I miss you.

14:59.004 --> 15:01.324
We still love each other.

15:02.724 --> 15:05.324
And it seems like...

15:06.883 --> 15:08.863
..the least worst option.

15:08.963 --> 15:10.963
(LAUGHS) Wow!

15:12.003 --> 15:15.863
I'm just a boy
standing in front of a girl,

15:15.963 --> 15:19.343
hearing that
I'm the least worst option.

15:19.443 --> 15:22.443
(TENDER MUSIC)

15:32.643 --> 15:35.563
-Want to go upstairs?
-Yep.

15:39.803 --> 15:42.942
(CRIES)

15:43.042 --> 15:45.502
ANGIE ON RECORDING: Hi. You've
reached Angie. Leave a message.

15:45.602 --> 15:47.602
(LINE BEEPS)

15:48.722 --> 15:51.622
What's going on, Ol?
We're starting in two minutes.

15:51.722 --> 15:53.462
Yeah, she was supposed to be
here ages ago.

15:53.562 --> 15:56.422
-What about your dad?
-He's not answering.

15:56.522 --> 15:59.042
-(CRIES)
-Santi's at work.

16:00.282 --> 16:03.882
-Can I be on the team, Weema?
-(CRIES)

16:06.242 --> 16:08.242
OK.

16:11.642 --> 16:14.362
-(STUDENTS APPLAUD)
-(BABY CRIES)

16:16.201 --> 16:19.201
(TENSE MUSIC)

16:28.481 --> 16:33.141
Our opponents believe that clear
examination is a waste of time,

16:33.241 --> 16:35.421
however,
we on the affirmative contend

16:35.521 --> 16:37.341
that on closer examination,

16:37.441 --> 16:38.741
it is obvious
that global failures...

16:38.841 --> 16:40.341
-(BABY SCREAMS)
-..to intervene...

16:40.441 --> 16:42.861
-You want me to take her?
-No, no, no. It's fine.

16:42.961 --> 16:43.861
(STUDENTS WHISPER)

16:43.961 --> 16:45.861
OLY: Thank you.

16:45.961 --> 16:47.961
(STUDENTS WHISPER)

16:48.961 --> 16:50.960
(SOFTLY) Do you want
to hold him?

16:52.080 --> 16:54.900
(LOUDLY) However,
we on the affirmative contend

16:55.000 --> 16:56.540
that on closer examination,

16:56.640 --> 17:00.340
it is obvious global failures to
intervene in humanitarian crises

17:00.440 --> 17:03.140
have been compounded by
the lack of conceptual consensus

17:03.240 --> 17:05.260
on the scope of
the responsibility to protect

17:05.360 --> 17:07.100
and on the meaning
of women's rights,

17:07.200 --> 17:10.060
which has led at best
to negative outcomes

17:10.160 --> 17:14.320
and at worst to unchecked
genocide on a global scale.

17:19.880 --> 17:22.240
(CRIES)

17:23.600 --> 17:26.019
-That was amazing.
-Killed it, Oly.

17:26.119 --> 17:28.919
Um, I'm just gonna step out
for a second.

17:30.519 --> 17:33.779
ADJUDICATOR: OK, let's have the
third speaker for the negative.

17:33.879 --> 17:35.879
-When you're ready.
-(WHISPERS) We got this.

17:41.159 --> 17:42.339
Where were you?

17:42.439 --> 17:47.139
Oh! Oh, sorry. How'd you go?

17:47.239 --> 17:49.939
Mum, I just had to do
the whole debate holding J

17:50.039 --> 17:52.259
while she tried to eat
my debating cards.

17:52.359 --> 17:53.979
(GROANS)

17:54.079 --> 17:57.139
We won, no thanks to you.

17:57.239 --> 18:00.198
Oh, well, that's a good result.

18:01.838 --> 18:04.738
Do you know how hard it is to be
the schoolgirl with a baby?

18:04.838 --> 18:07.818
Everyone thinks that
they know you,

18:07.918 --> 18:10.618
that they can see
exactly who you are.

18:10.718 --> 18:12.338
DOM: Hey, peanut!

18:12.438 --> 18:16.538
And where were you? I called
you both, like, six times!

18:16.638 --> 18:19.698
Sorry, darling, but we were
looking for Turtle...

18:19.798 --> 18:22.378
..at first,
and then your mum and I...

18:22.478 --> 18:24.458
We found him, actually,
but then we...

18:24.558 --> 18:26.938
Let him go and we...

18:27.038 --> 18:28.418
Turtle?

18:28.518 --> 18:31.378
Yeah. Garry's bird.

18:31.478 --> 18:34.138
You know? Garry Robinson.

18:34.238 --> 18:36.237
Unbelievable.

18:37.117 --> 18:38.417
Where are you going?

18:38.517 --> 18:40.617
I'm gonna go be with someone
who loves me and J

18:40.717 --> 18:42.837
more than some
rando's pet cockatiel.

18:46.637 --> 18:48.297
(MATIAS SPEAKS SPANISH)

18:48.397 --> 18:50.397
(DOOR CLOSES)

18:51.797 --> 18:53.777
Hey!

18:53.877 --> 18:55.457
Glad you could join us.

18:55.557 --> 18:58.657
-What's that supposed to mean?
-Means you're late.

18:58.757 --> 19:00.977
Chill out, yeah. I'm here now.

19:01.077 --> 19:04.357
-Hi, Ita.
-You smell like a pub.

19:07.477 --> 19:09.056
-Hey, guys.
-Hey.

19:09.156 --> 19:10.496
-How are you, man?
-GABRIEL: Good.

19:10.596 --> 19:12.596
Hey, Seb.

19:14.796 --> 19:16.796
You all right, Dad?

19:20.276 --> 19:22.276
Is there something
you want to say?

19:23.036 --> 19:25.936
Bueno. It's our anniversary
and we're going out dancing.

19:26.036 --> 19:30.096
I would love to have a nice
dinner like normal people.

19:30.196 --> 19:32.196
Your anniversary, huh?

19:35.276 --> 19:37.276
That's cute.

19:37.716 --> 19:39.716
True love wins, huh?

19:40.196 --> 19:42.296
Dad said there's no way
I'm leaving school

19:42.396 --> 19:44.935
unless it's to play in
the Copa Libertadores.

19:45.035 --> 19:46.495
Mm-hm.

19:46.595 --> 19:47.895
That's interesting,

19:47.995 --> 19:50.015
'cause he hasn't mentioned
a word to me about it.

19:50.115 --> 19:52.295
Mate, come on. Let's just eat.

19:52.395 --> 19:54.335
Not one word.

19:54.435 --> 19:55.735
I can't win with you.

19:55.835 --> 19:57.835
Have you got an opinion on
what I'm doing?

19:59.315 --> 20:02.415
I'm working, I'm making money,
I'm trying, right?

20:02.515 --> 20:04.575
I'm doing everything I can
for my family

20:04.675 --> 20:07.695
and I come home and I get
a "Glad you could join us"

20:07.795 --> 20:09.795
from him, of all people

20:14.795 --> 20:17.095
You're just a hypocrite.

20:17.195 --> 20:20.534
You've been drinking.
Is that my fault too, is it?

20:20.634 --> 20:24.734
You really want to know?
I'm a teacher.

20:24.834 --> 20:27.174
How am I ever gonna be OK with
you dropping out of school?

20:27.274 --> 20:30.994
But it's your life. You have to
take responsibility for it.

20:35.394 --> 20:40.854
Ita, you know, I had a dream
about Mum last night.

20:40.954 --> 20:43.254
She's really proud
that I got a job.

20:43.354 --> 20:47.254
Your mother's always
proud of you. Always.

20:47.354 --> 20:48.854
Thanks, Ita.

20:48.954 --> 20:51.014
She's happy that I left school.

20:51.114 --> 20:52.814
She would have hated you
dropping out of school!

20:52.914 --> 20:54.133
-(ITA GASPS)
-ALEJANDRO: Matias!

20:54.233 --> 20:56.533
You were just a little kid!
I knew her!

20:56.633 --> 20:58.633
I knew her better than anyone!

21:01.033 --> 21:03.153
Ah, fuck this.

21:12.073 --> 21:14.053
GABRIEL: Well, that went badly.

21:14.153 --> 21:16.153
(SEBASTIAN LAUGHS)

21:21.233 --> 21:23.133
Hey, what's going on?

21:23.233 --> 21:25.573
I'm not staying there.
My dad's fucked.

21:25.673 --> 21:28.292
OK, well, we were
supposed to stay over.

21:28.392 --> 21:30.132
Were you gonna tell me
that you're going out?

21:30.232 --> 21:32.012
-I don't fucking know, Oly.
-OK. Hey!

21:32.112 --> 21:33.932
-What?!
-Do not take this out on me, OK?

21:34.032 --> 21:35.932
I just had to do that
whole debate holding J

21:36.032 --> 21:37.852
because my parents stood me up
for a parrot

21:37.952 --> 21:39.492
and you were at work

21:39.592 --> 21:41.692
and I got some really bad news
this week.

21:41.792 --> 21:45.612
What? What bad news did you get?

21:45.712 --> 21:48.652
I didn't get
this Canberra internship?

21:48.752 --> 21:50.752
What internship?

21:52.152 --> 21:54.612
-I was gonna tell you about it.
-When?

21:54.712 --> 21:55.892
When were you gonna tell me

21:55.992 --> 21:57.292
that you applied for
an internship?

21:57.392 --> 21:59.372
Were you planning on taking J
with you to Canberra?

21:59.472 --> 22:01.572
OK, well, you didn't tell me
that you applied for your job.

22:01.672 --> 22:03.091
Yeah, but, Oly,
we talked about it.

22:03.191 --> 22:05.751
Yeah, but you decided unilaterally.
What, I don't get to do that?

22:07.351 --> 22:10.371
I'm not just going to abandon
my dreams and be some loser...

22:10.471 --> 22:12.771
-Who drops out of school.
-No! That is not what I said.

22:12.871 --> 22:15.731
I dropped out of school for you
and J, to take care of us.

22:15.831 --> 22:17.731
And I never asked you
to do that.

22:17.831 --> 22:19.211
That was your decision.

22:19.311 --> 22:21.791
I just want to be able
to make my own decisions.

22:23.591 --> 22:25.291
Oly. Oly. Oly, stop.

22:25.391 --> 22:27.391
Oly.

22:33.511 --> 22:35.291
I'm sorry.

22:35.391 --> 22:37.391
Come here.

22:38.630 --> 22:40.630
I'm sorry.

22:44.150 --> 22:45.530
OK?

22:45.630 --> 22:47.630
You're right.

22:50.310 --> 22:52.310
You should be able
to make those choices.

22:54.230 --> 22:57.650
(SNIFFS) I really don't want
to fight with you, OK?

22:57.750 --> 23:02.590
I mean, it's you that
was fighting, but good call.

23:09.950 --> 23:13.309
Oly, you and J...

23:15.429 --> 23:17.829
..it's the first time I've been
happy since I lost my mum.

23:21.749 --> 23:24.609
I'm glad, 'cause... (SIGHS)

23:24.709 --> 23:26.729
..my parents
are driving me insane.

23:26.829 --> 23:28.889
(LAUGHS) What's new?

23:28.989 --> 23:30.989
(BOTH LAUGH)

23:35.069 --> 23:38.669
Oly, move out with me.

23:40.949 --> 23:42.329
What?

23:42.429 --> 23:44.429
Let's get our own place.

23:48.188 --> 23:50.208
Like, now?

23:50.308 --> 23:52.588
-Like, before the HSC?
-Yeah.

23:54.228 --> 23:56.228
Me, you and J.

23:58.108 --> 24:00.108
I just want us to be together.

24:00.948 --> 24:03.148
(GENTLE, MELANCHOLY MUSIC)

24:12.668 --> 24:14.668
Matias...

24:28.107 --> 24:30.107
(SNIFFS)

24:55.347 --> 24:57.326
(BOWIE SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)

24:57.426 --> 24:59.286
-Hi!
-ANGIE: Oh, look who's here.

24:59.386 --> 25:00.886
-Hey!
-SANTI: Hey!

25:00.986 --> 25:02.406
-SANTI: Good morning!
-How are you?

25:02.506 --> 25:05.846
-We've got some news.
-DOM: Ooh. What's the news?

25:05.946 --> 25:10.286
OK, so, Mum, Dad,
don't freak out, OK?

25:10.386 --> 25:11.966
We've decided and
you can't change our minds.

25:12.066 --> 25:13.686
-SANTI: Yep.
-(BABY GRIZZLES)

25:13.786 --> 25:16.286
Santi and I are gonna
get our own place.

25:16.386 --> 25:19.446
What? You can't.

25:19.546 --> 25:21.646
We've done the maths and we can
get a one-bedroom place

25:21.746 --> 25:24.966
for $350, maybe $450 a week
and with my new job, it's...

25:25.066 --> 25:26.806
And I'm gonna go back
to tutoring

25:26.906 --> 25:29.606
and J can stay with Bernardita
or you guys a few days a week.

25:29.706 --> 25:31.846
-(KETTLE WHISTLES)
-Go ahead.

25:31.946 --> 25:34.025
I need some space anyway.

25:40.025 --> 25:44.165
This is the Champions League
Premiership of terrible ideas.

25:44.265 --> 25:45.805
They're just kids.

25:45.905 --> 25:49.605
Well, they've got to make their
own mistakes, I guess, you know?

25:49.705 --> 25:52.125
Let 'em touch the hotplate.

25:52.225 --> 25:53.845
What, so they don't do it again?

25:53.945 --> 25:55.945
Well, it's one way to learn.

26:00.265 --> 26:02.865
Well, she's not taking
our teapot.

26:04.585 --> 26:08.404
No, 'cause the blue one
gets a drip when it pours.

26:08.504 --> 26:10.504
(CHUCKLES)

26:10.984 --> 26:13.144
(JOYFUL MUSIC)

26:20.464 --> 26:21.684
Where do you want it, mate?

26:21.784 --> 26:23.784
Uh, just in here.

26:25.864 --> 26:27.044
DOM: Looking good.

26:27.144 --> 26:29.324
SONG: ♪ We can leave
this place... ♪

26:29.424 --> 26:31.884
-Is this your room?
-Yeah. Thank you.

26:31.984 --> 26:34.364
Just put it like that.
Pleasure, treasure.

26:34.464 --> 26:37.564
(DOM GRUNTS)

26:37.664 --> 26:40.104
Where does this go?

26:44.263 --> 26:48.543
Don't put there. Put here.

26:51.063 --> 26:53.063
(GROWLS SOFTLY) Diabla.

26:57.023 --> 26:58.083
(SIGHS)

26:58.183 --> 27:00.723
I don't know where
I'm gonna put my desk.

27:00.823 --> 27:03.283
You can study at my place.

27:03.383 --> 27:05.383
Thanks.

27:08.223 --> 27:09.683
Are you OK?

27:09.783 --> 27:12.083
Yeah.

27:12.183 --> 27:14.183
(SIGHS)

27:16.582 --> 27:17.522
OK.

27:17.622 --> 27:19.442
I'll take it. Ta.

27:19.542 --> 27:21.542
-Thanks, mate.
-(CAR DOORS SHUT)

27:23.942 --> 27:25.942
-Hey.
-Hey.

27:27.142 --> 27:30.362
-This is it.
-Yeah.

27:30.462 --> 27:32.462
This is it.

27:33.582 --> 27:36.122
I'm just coming to
wish you good luck.

27:36.222 --> 27:38.362
Thanks.

27:38.462 --> 27:40.722
Ita's got J on Monday, yeah?

27:40.822 --> 27:42.822
-Yep.
-Good.

27:58.941 --> 28:00.941
Get in there.

28:10.781 --> 28:13.761
-(ENGINE STARTS)
-VINCE: Big day, eh?

28:13.861 --> 28:16.681
-You'll be OK?
-Yeah.

28:16.781 --> 28:18.601
Yeah, no, no,
we're gonna be good, man.

28:18.701 --> 28:21.741
You guys are great, yeah?

28:23.381 --> 28:25.281
Well, G-G-G-G-G-G-G...

28:25.381 --> 28:27.380
BOTH: G-G-G-G-G-G-G-Unit.

28:28.500 --> 28:30.500
Let's finish these boxes, yeah?

28:31.460 --> 28:33.200
I brought your favourite mug.

28:33.300 --> 28:34.600
Oh.

28:34.700 --> 28:38.120
And made you a pasta
for dinner tonight.

28:38.220 --> 28:40.160
Just a quick...quick cannelloni.

28:40.260 --> 28:42.360
I've got some toilet rolls,

28:42.460 --> 28:44.200
nappies,

28:44.300 --> 28:47.120
some new toothbrushes
for you and Santi.

28:47.220 --> 28:51.080
You know, just anything you
might need for your first night.

28:51.180 --> 28:52.520
Thanks, Mum.

28:52.620 --> 28:55.600
(ANGIE SIGHS)

28:55.700 --> 28:57.040
Why didn't you tell me

28:57.140 --> 28:59.260
that you and Dad
were getting back together?

29:00.460 --> 29:02.859
Would it have made
any difference?

29:04.099 --> 29:07.879
I'm really sorry for saying that
you were the worst mother alive.

29:07.979 --> 29:09.759
You're not.

29:09.859 --> 29:13.859
You are the opposite of that.

29:15.899 --> 29:17.899
Oh.

29:19.219 --> 29:21.959
I don't know
if I can do this, Mum.

29:22.059 --> 29:25.099
There's so much else
that I'd like to do.

29:27.619 --> 29:29.619
You're doing it, Ol.

29:31.259 --> 29:34.079
To be a mum is to be divided -

29:34.179 --> 29:38.638
your energy, your time,
your heart.

29:38.738 --> 29:40.278
(SIGHS)

29:40.378 --> 29:44.598
You trade freedom for love.

29:44.698 --> 29:47.558
-Is it worth it?
-(CHUCKLES)

29:47.658 --> 29:49.918
Mm, depends when you ask me.

29:50.018 --> 29:53.618
(LAUGHS) Yeah, of course it is.

29:55.698 --> 29:57.118
I'm gonna go.

29:57.218 --> 29:59.218
Mwah!

30:03.578 --> 30:04.638
(SIGHS)

30:04.738 --> 30:07.158
Santi... (SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)

30:07.258 --> 30:10.038
I will. OK. Thank you, Ita.

30:10.138 --> 30:12.137
-Bye.
-Bye, darling.

30:14.017 --> 30:16.017
-Bye, darling.
-See you, bro.

30:16.537 --> 30:19.477
-Text me if you need anything.
-Yeah, I will. Thank you.

30:19.577 --> 30:21.157
-See youse all.
-See you, bro.

30:21.257 --> 30:22.517
Thanks for all
the heavy lifting.

30:22.617 --> 30:24.117
-I'll walk you home?
-All right.

30:24.217 --> 30:25.637
Yeah, I'm walking
that way anyway.

30:25.737 --> 30:26.837
Oh, yeah.

30:26.937 --> 30:28.277
Auntie Weema.

30:28.377 --> 30:31.737
('PERRA DEL FUTURA'
BY TOMASA DEL REAL)

30:34.737 --> 30:37.377
(TOMASA DEL REAL
SINGS IN SPANISH)

30:43.257 --> 30:45.297
-Here we are.
-Here we are.

30:46.656 --> 30:50.396
-This is gonna be awesome.
-Yeah, just the three of us.

30:50.496 --> 30:53.496
('PERRA DEL FUTURA'
CONTINUES IN SPANISH)

31:05.136 --> 31:08.036
('PERRA DEL FUTURA'
CONTINUES IN SPANISH)
